==English==
===Etymology===
from Late Latin [[annihilatus]], perfect participle of [[anihilare]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-annihilate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
'''to annihilate'''

#to reduce to [[nothing]], to [[destroy]], to [[eradicate]]
''
The Protestants of the North fear they will be annihilated by the Catholics should Britain withdraw from Ulster.''
